{THELWALL } It is said that in the year 920 AD King Edward (The Elder) camped here on the way to Manchester. He thought it was a good place to camp and conferred on it the title of{CITY.}
{THELWALL MORRIS DANCERS } The team is made up of 6 _ 8 menwho wear white shirts and socks with trousers sawn_off at the knees. They carry sticks or handkerchiefs which they wave about.The group has been in existence for about 12 years.
{THELWALL ROSE QUEEN} A Disco is held in the village annually. At the dance a name is drawn from a hatfull of nominations. The lucky teenage girl becomes Rose Queen for the year and leads the annual Walking-day procession through the village.
